\section{Counterexamples to Translations}
In this section I will provide visual aid for counterexamples of operators that are not valid up to Strong Bisimularity.
\subsection{Interrupt Operator}
A counterexample to the encoding of the Interrupt Operator being Strongly Bisimilar is with the trivial example
\[P = \tau,\,Q = b\]
This should yield the following process graph:

		\circ && \bullet \\
		\\
		\bullet && \bullet
		\arrow["\tau"', color={rgb,255:red,214;green,92;blue,92}, from=1-1, to=1-3]

\subsection{Throw Operator}

\[P = \tau, Q = b\]
